{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778191094,"nonce":"2D05B9RffuXb7c+99USBPyLHw/I=","message":"**First induced-gain run on Part 2.5 checkpoints — cross-cutting findings.** Issue `6fdf9a4`, commit `36aa1ad`, auth `cab29866`. 10 training-method groups × 3 `w` channels (af = additive_force, sd = structural_da, sp = sensory_perturbation) × `qr_cost` z. All 30 cells converged in power iteration.\n\n**Three cross-cutting findings that change the analysis-side picture:**\n\n1. **`additive_force × qr_cost` (γ_af) is NOT a sensitive cross-method discriminator on a single canonical reach.** All non-outlier groups: γ_af ∈ [0.124, 0.248] (factor ~2 spread, ~9–18× γ⋆). Standard backprop, vanilla, minimax seeds, mult_pop5, and ratio03 all sit within this band. The H∞ norm on the *trained-against* channel does not separate flavor-(a) minimax from standard backprop on this geometry. Doesn't deprecate the analysis — but the channel that was assumed primary is the *least* informative empirically.\n\n2. **`sensory_perturbation × qr_cost` (γ_sp) cleanly separates minimax from non-minimax.** Minimax seeds: γ_sp ∈ [1.32, 2.14]; vanilla/baseline: γ_sp ∈ [2.61, 4.40]. ~2× better attenuation in minimax-trained networks. **This becomes the de-facto headline channel** for cross-method comparison empirically. Tier-promote: `sensory_perturbation × qr_cost` is the empirical headline for training-method discrimination, NOT `additive_force × qr_cost`.\n\n3. **`structural_da × qr_cost` (γ_sd) is uniformly large (~150–170) across all training methods.** Consistent with the absence of flavor-(b) training in the current batch. The structural-uncertainty channel cannot discriminate (a) from (b) until a flavor-(b)-trained network exists for comparison — i.e., until `97c227a` (Riccati B_w lift) and/or `c723082` (LinearDynamicsAdversary) produce a checkpoint. Until then γ_sd values are uninformative absolute numbers across the board.\n\n**(a) ⊊ (b) thesis empirical status:** NOT established by this run. The structural_da channel measures *closed-loop sensitivity* given the trained network — it does not distinguish flavor-(a) and flavor-(b) training a priori. Sharp test of (a) ⊊ (b) is blocked on producing at least one flavor-(b)-trained network (`c723082`).\n\n**Test-coverage finding (cross-link to `b131510` audit):** synthetic-Graph unit test passed but real `SimpleFeedback` integration broke on `_call_single_step` cycle wires. New issue filed for the adapter fix; the audit's \"5-line wrapper\" claim was incomplete because the unit test didn't exercise cycle paths. Worth noting as a generic rigor lesson: integration smoke tests on real-shaped graphs are needed, not just synthetic scaffolding.\n\n**Companion findings filed as separate issues:** adapter cycle-wires fix (just-filed); mult_single replicate-0 outlier (just-filed).","files":null}]}